SUMMARY—Revises provisions relating to county hospitals and
county hospital districts. (BDR 40-559)
FISCAL NOTE: Effect on Local Government: No.
Effect on the State: No.
~
EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to health care; revising provisions governing the
employment and training of certain providers of health
care by a county hospital or county hospital district;
authorizing a county or district hospital to contract for the
provision of certain services; authorizing a county or
district hospital to form a separate organization for certain
purposes; and providing other matters properly relating
thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law authorizes a county or group of counties to establish a public
2 hospital. (NRS 450.020) Existing law also authorizes a board of county
3 commissioners to establish a county hospital district to operate a district hospital or
4 otherwise provide the services of a hospital to the residents of this State. (NRS
5 450.590, 450.610, 450.630, 450.710) Existing law authorizes the governing body of
6 a county hospital to: (1) employ physicians, interns and dentists, on a full-time or
7 part-time basis, and fix their compensations; and (2) control the admission of such
8 physicians and interns to the staff of the hospital by promulgating appropriate rules,
9 regulations and standards governing those appointments. (NRS 450.180) Existing
10 law similarly authorizes the governing body of a county hospital district to take
11 such actions with regard to physicians and interns. (NRS 450.640) Existing law
12 further authorizes the governing body of a county hospital to institute and maintain
13 training programs in the county hospital for resident physicians, interns and
14 postgraduates that meet certain accreditation standards. (NRS 450.455) Section 3
15 of this bill additionally authorizes the governing body of a county hospital district
16 to employ and fix the compensation of dentists. Sections 1 and 3 of this bill
17 remove interns from the list of persons that the governing body of a county hospital
18 or county hospital district may employ, and instead, authorizes such a governing
19 body to employ and control the admission of medical and dental residents and
