21 hospital to institute and maintain training programs for fellows in addition to
22 resident physicians. Section 2 also updates the name of an accrediting organization
23 for medical residencies.
24 Existing law authorizes a county or district hospital to enter into a contract to
25 provide certain services in connection with or related to the operation of certain
26 hospitals or necessary for the health and welfare of the general public. (NRS
27 450.800) Section 4 of this bill specifies that such services include certain mental or
28 behavioral health services performed in connection with or related to a crisis
29 stabilization center, which is a hospital with an endorsement to provide such
30 services. (NRS 449.0915) Section 4 also authorizes a county or district hospital to
31 form a separate organization to provide or contract for the provision of certain
32 services.
